# Issue #83 sub-case 3c — call-site without enough info.
# The caller's binding is unrefined (`x: Int`), so the analysis has
# no static fact to discharge the callee's `requires b != 0`. The
# runtime assert inside `divide` stays in place; the
# `--dump-call-elision` report records `runtime` for this site.
# The compile succeeds — strictness is opt-in via the caller's
# refinement.

fn divide(a: Int, b: Int) : Int requires b != 0 = a / b

fn use_unrefined(x: Int) : Int = divide(10, x)
